WEBVTT

00:04.498 --> 00:06.866
(Islamic call to prayer over loudspeaker)

00:13.974 --> 00:16.308
(prayer continues in distance)

00:20.113 --> 00:22.582
- (door bangs)
- MAN: Call the American embassy.

00:22.583 --> 00:25.452
(speaking Arabic)

00:25.453 --> 00:27.354
<i>Call the State Department.</i>

00:27.355 --> 00:29.189
You can't do this.

00:29.190 --> 00:30.957
You know, we have rights.

00:30.958 --> 00:33.625
- Call the American embassy.
- (men shouting in Arabic)

00:37.097 --> 00:38.935
I don't understand... what'd he say?

00:38.936 --> 00:43.735
He said, "Don't be a fool.
You're gonna die here."

00:51.411 --> 00:53.346
- Dr. McCord.
- Yeah.

00:53.347 --> 00:55.348
Hey, can I talk to you about my thesis?

00:55.349 --> 00:57.684
Uh, sure... during office hours.

00:57.685 --> 00:59.452
Yeah, your office hours
don't really work for me.

00:59.453 --> 01:00.920
(laughs) Sorry to hear that.

01:00.921 --> 01:03.690
Thing is, I don't really want
to write about the Cold War.

01:03.691 --> 01:05.592
You're aware that the class is called

01:05.593 --> 01:07.694
"Postwar Politics and the Cold War."

01:07.695 --> 01:10.263
Yeah, but I feel like it's been done.

01:10.264 --> 01:13.333
That's why they call it history, Jake.

01:13.334 --> 01:15.835
Thing is, my theory is that

01:15.836 --> 01:17.770
we are living through a new cold war.

01:17.771 --> 01:19.806
All right, compare and
contrast to the original

01:19.807 --> 01:21.040
and convince me.

01:21.041 --> 01:23.137
Great. Also, I'll need
an extension. My parents

01:23.138 --> 01:25.211
are coming to town and
they're very needy.

01:25.212 --> 01:26.512
Oh. My husband bought tickets

01:26.513 --> 01:27.947
to the opera this weekend.

01:27.948 --> 01:30.049
I mean, normally, I love the
opera, but I got to tell you,

01:30.050 --> 01:31.851
it's been a hell of a week,
and the thought of sitting

01:31.852 --> 01:33.553
in a dimly lit room with a bunch of people

01:33.554 --> 01:35.488
singing at me in Italian...

01:35.489 --> 01:37.490
it's just gonna make me fall asleep.

01:37.491 --> 01:38.825
I'm so sorry.

01:38.826 --> 01:41.627
I thought we were telling
each other our problems.

01:41.628 --> 01:43.029
No extension.

01:43.030 --> 01:44.925
Enjoy your parents.

01:44.926 --> 01:46.260
MAN: <i>What Aquinas was trying to say</i>

01:46.261 --> 01:48.528
in <i> Summa Theologica</i> is that existence

01:48.529 --> 01:51.031
and essence are separate things, right?

01:51.032 --> 01:53.900
That's the whole notion behind
Catholic transubstantiation.

01:53.901 --> 01:55.802
Now, Luther though a Thomist

01:55.803 --> 01:57.304
by definition, departed from him

01:57.305 --> 01:58.422
- in significant ways.
- Honey?

01:58.423 --> 02:00.091
Their eyes are glazing over.

02:00.092 --> 02:02.776
They're just listening to
you 'cause you're so cute.

02:02.777 --> 02:04.244
GIRL: No way.

02:04.245 --> 02:06.246
I hated religion before I took his class.

02:06.247 --> 02:07.881
Now I'm totally caught up.

02:07.882 --> 02:09.082
He's brilliant.

02:09.083 --> 02:12.319
Wow. Well, do you mind if I just

02:12.320 --> 02:14.087
steal his brilliance for a minute?

02:14.088 --> 02:15.854
Yeah, sure.

02:17.290 --> 02:19.593
So, how am I supposed to
develop a cult following?

02:19.594 --> 02:21.372
Oh, I think you'll figure it out.

02:21.373 --> 02:23.964
Hey, listen. Did you remember
you got to cook tonight?

02:23.965 --> 02:25.131
'Cause I'm going into DC.

02:25.132 --> 02:26.493
- Right, the spy reunion.
- Yes.

02:26.494 --> 02:29.202
And since I'm the only one
who can talk about work,

02:29.203 --> 02:30.270
I get to be

02:30.271 --> 02:31.638
the center of attention.

02:31.639 --> 02:33.506
You're always the center
of attention with me.

02:33.507 --> 02:36.074
Really? Tell that
to your cult following.

02:36.776 --> 02:39.011
WOMAN: <i>You wouldn't recognize the CIA.</i>

02:39.012 --> 02:41.414
George is the only one
on a Middle East desk right now.

02:41.415 --> 02:42.649
MAN: Libya.

02:42.650 --> 02:44.818
Lebanon. I'm staring at screens

02:44.819 --> 02:46.619
of abandoned factories and oil wells,

02:46.620 --> 02:49.422
listening to chatter
about the World Cup.

02:49.423 --> 02:51.124
I mean, they could at least have

02:51.125 --> 02:52.612
pastured me somewhere interesting.

02:52.613 --> 02:55.828
- He loves that desk job.
- They didn't pasture you.

02:55.829 --> 02:57.096
They just didn't feel like

02:57.097 --> 02:58.765
risking your life
in the field anymore.

02:58.766 --> 02:59.932
You bought their story?

02:59.933 --> 03:02.101
There was no evidence
that my cover was blown.

03:02.102 --> 03:03.136
He never looks back.

03:03.137 --> 03:04.437
And you guys should talk.

03:04.438 --> 03:05.705
They both got Africa.

03:05.706 --> 03:06.739
Do you know how volatile

03:06.740 --> 03:07.707
- that place is gonna be?
- Yes!

03:07.708 --> 03:08.708
That is like the disco

03:08.709 --> 03:10.042
of global hot spots.

03:10.043 --> 03:11.511
- Oh, yeah.
- Why don't you call

03:11.512 --> 03:12.912
our, uh, former boss and complain

03:12.913 --> 03:14.280
to him about your desk job?

03:14.281 --> 03:16.716
- Oh, I did.
- George!

03:16.717 --> 03:19.318
- You called POTUS about your desk job?
- I... I...

03:19.319 --> 03:21.254
I gave it a shot, okay? I mean, he ran

03:21.255 --> 03:22.655
the place for 12 years, I figured

03:22.656 --> 03:24.557
he's still invested in personnel, so...

03:24.558 --> 03:26.025
He never called back.

03:26.026 --> 03:27.303
Imagine that.

03:27.304 --> 03:28.761
How is the, uh, bucolic life going?

03:28.762 --> 03:30.162
It's great.

03:30.163 --> 03:31.964
We're teachers.

03:31.965 --> 03:33.232
We're parents.

03:33.233 --> 03:34.652
We're horse owners.

03:34.653 --> 03:36.035
- Mmm.
- Ooh! Oh, my!

03:36.036 --> 03:37.636
And every morning we wake up,

03:37.637 --> 03:40.406
- that's all we got to be.
- (phones buzzing)

03:40.407 --> 03:41.639
That's a shock.

03:45.144 --> 03:47.679
Well, this can't be good.

03:49.782 --> 03:51.750
The, uh, Secretary of State's plane

03:51.751 --> 03:54.018
just went down over the Atlantic.

03:56.281 --> 03:57.259
HENRY: <i>Hey!</i>

03:57.260 --> 03:58.657
I thought we said no
gadgets at the table.

03:58.658 --> 03:59.925
ELIZABETH: We did.

03:59.926 --> 04:01.867
And then the kids
never came to the table.

04:01.868 --> 04:04.229
Besides, it's Saturday.

04:04.230 --> 04:05.230
Oh, yay!

04:05.231 --> 04:07.232
No Rules Saturday?

04:07.233 --> 04:09.001
REPORTER: Vincent Marsh,
of course, began...

04:09.002 --> 04:10.235
- Hey!
- Dad, can you turn it off?

04:10.236 --> 04:13.038
What? My screen is
competing with your screens?

04:13.039 --> 04:15.908
<i>Repeating what we know so far...</i>

04:15.909 --> 04:18.744
the Secretary of State Vincent
Marsh's plane disappeared

04:18.745 --> 04:20.345
<i>off the coast of Florida.</i>

04:20.346 --> 04:23.582
He was headed to Caracas, Venezuela.

04:23.583 --> 04:25.184
Mom, do you think it was terrorism?

04:25.185 --> 04:26.985
No.

04:26.986 --> 04:28.723
I think people shouldn't
fly in small planes.

04:28.724 --> 04:30.422
Still, why was he going to Venezuela?

04:30.423 --> 04:32.399
- Is that a resort destination?
- JASON: Exactly.

04:32.400 --> 04:35.102
When will you guys acknowledge
the obvious conspiracy around us

04:35.103 --> 04:36.561
- at all times?
- Seriously?

04:36.562 --> 04:38.363
You had to wind up the anarchist?

04:38.364 --> 04:39.831
Sorry.

04:39.832 --> 04:42.132
(horse snorts)

04:45.864 --> 04:47.806
I thought you were gonna do
something relaxing today.

04:47.807 --> 04:49.841
Well, this relaxes me.

04:49.842 --> 04:51.042
Oh, uh, your phone.

04:51.043 --> 04:52.778
It wouldn't stop ringing,
so I answered it.

04:52.779 --> 04:54.279
Well, who is it?

04:54.280 --> 04:56.414
Some lady says it's the
president's office.

04:56.415 --> 04:57.782
PTA?

04:57.783 --> 04:59.184
The United States.

04:59.185 --> 05:01.419
Well, that's a prank. Hang it up.

05:01.420 --> 05:03.421
Just take it. She sounds serious.

05:03.422 --> 05:05.722
(siren chirps nearby)

05:08.059 --> 05:10.394
(horse snorts)

05:14.799 --> 05:16.735
(dog barking in distance)

05:16.736 --> 05:19.036
(vehicles approaching)

